gcloud functions deploy run_sql ^
--gen2 ^
--region=us-central1 ^
--runtime=python312 ^
--source=. ^
--entry-point=run_sql ^
--service-account=data-pipeline-user@musa5090s26-team4.iam.gserviceaccount.com ^
--memory=8Gi ^
--timeout=480s ^
--set-env-vars=RAW_DATA_BUCKET=musa5090s26-team4-raw_data,PREPARED_DATA_BUCKET=musa5090s26-team4-prepared_data,SOURCE_DATASET=source,CORE_DATASET=core ^
--trigger-http ^
--no-allow-unauthenticated


then run:
gcloud functions call run_sql

That deployed it and gave us the url to call it: https://us-central1-musa5090s26-team4.cloudfunctions.net/run_sql

Call functions by going to that url?sql=the_name_of_the_sql_you_want_to_run.sql

Or, use curl function in bash

curl -H "Authorization: bearer $(gcloud auth print-identity-token)" \
"https://us-central1-musa5090s26-team4.cloudfunctions.net/run_sql?sql=the_name_of_the_sql.sql"

You need to redeploy this function each time you add a sql file to the sql subfolder


To retrain model: in bash:
